OL,3,CMum on trial for murder: What it was
OL,4,Clike in the courtroom
OL,6,FAs the prosecuting barrister, Richard
OL,7,FWright KC, laid out the case on the
OL,8,Fopening day, it became clear that
OL,9,Ffollowing this case would be
OL,10,Ftraumatic: for the jury, for the legal
OL,11,Fteams, for the public who read or
OL,12,Fwatched the coverage, and for
OL,13,Fjournalists like myself who have sat
OL,14,Fin court or followed the case over
OL,15,Fvideo link.
OL,17,FTraumatic too for Dwelaniyah's father,
OL,18,FGabriel Adu-Appau, who sat in the
OL,19,Fpublic gallery for much of the trial,
OL,20,Flistening to the evidence against the
OL,21,Fmother of his children.
