OL,3,CMum on trial for murder: What it was
OL,4,Clike in the courtroom
OL,6,FDespite her apparent religious
OL,7,Fconvictions she chose not to 'swear by
OL,8,FAlmighty God', but to 'sincerely and
OL,9,Ftruly declare and affirm' that she
OL,10,Fwould tell the truth, the whole truth
OL,11,Fand nothing but the truth.
OL,13,FAnd when she gave evidence, responding
OL,14,Fto questions from her barrister Jamie
OL,15,FHill KC, it was with a soft West
OL,16,FMidlands accent, occasionally
OL,17,Frequiring a reminder to speak up.
