OL,3,CMum on trial for murder: What it was
OL,4,Clike in the courtroom
OL,6,FHer tone level and calm, and never
OL,7,Fbetraying any sign of emotion, she
OL,8,Ftold lie after lie: that Dwelaniyah
OL,9,Fhad been burned playing in the shower,
OL,10,Fthat she hadn't shaken him on the day
OL,11,Fhe died.
OL,13,FThat calm demeanour, present from the
OL,14,Fvery first time police spoke to her.
OL,16,FAnd then, after two-and-a-half weeks
OL,17,Fof evidence - and nine hours in the
OL,18,Fwitness box - she took a decision that
OL,19,Fsuggested she was anything but calm,
OL,20,Fand sacked her legal team.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/11
