OL,3,CMum on trial for murder: What it was
OL,4,Clike in the courtroom
OL,6,FWith her sat at the bench where her
OL,7,Fbarrister had been up to that point,
OL,8,Fthe judge told the jury: "Ms Robinson
OL,9,Fhas decided to dispense with the
OL,10,Fservices of her barristers and
OL,11,Fsolicitors. She's entitled to do that."
OL,13,FHe added that "she decided to sack,
OL,14,Feffectively, her solicitors and
OL,15,Fbarristers".
OL,17,FAs a result, instead of Jamie Hill KC
OL,18,Fpresenting the defence's closing
OL,19,Fspeech, Christina Robinson did so on
OL,20,Fher own behalf.
