OL,3,CMum on trial for murder: What it was
OL,4,Clike in the courtroom
OL,6,FA rambling and repetitive 68 minutes,
OL,7,Fit was like a scene from a bad
OL,8,FAmerican courtroom drama.
OL,10,F"I'll show to you today," she promised
OL,11,Fthe jury, "why I am not guilty and why
OL,12,Fthe case of the prosecution is simply
OL,13,Fnot true."
OL,15,FThe nub of her argument, that "despite
OL,16,Fwhat everyone has said", she claimed:
OL,17,F"There is nothing that directly
OL,18,Fincriminates me.
